king for\nexperienced and driven engineers who are excited for the challenge.\n\n# Requirements:\n\n  * US citizenship is required\n\n  * At least 5 years of experience in devops and/or infrastructure with increasing scope and responsibilities\n\n  * Experience with managing Kubernetes clusters using infrastructure as code (ideally Terraform)\n\n  * Experience with python, react + typescript, and ideally some C++ or CUDA\n\n  * Ability to empathize with development teams, understand the pain points in their workflows and create tools to accelerate them\n\n  * Strong interest in the devops/ML ops/infrastructure landscape; ability and willingness to assimilate state of the art and push it further\n\n  * A track record of proactively identifying and using opportunities to add value\n\n  * Ownership mindset\n\n# What you'll do\n\nYou will be personally responsible for managing all of the following:\n\n  * Git workflows / deployments / unit testing\n\n  * Customer support workflows and instrumentation - driving down issue response time\n\n  * Infrastructure deployments, be it new releases or the creation of new development workspaces\n\n  * ML ops\n\nPlease note: We are an equal opportunity employer and currently a remote-only\ncompany. At this time, we are focused on hiring primarily within the US, with\noccasional exception to accommodate exceptional talent.\n\n# What we offer:\n\n  * Interesting and challenging work\n\n  * Competitive salary and equity benefits\n\n  * Remote work with no commute\n\n  * Health, dental, and vision insurance\n\n  * Regular team events and offsites (~2x / year)\n\n  * Unlimited paid time off\n\n  * Paid parental leave\n\nWant to learn more about Quilter, our vision, and our investors? Visit our\nAbout page and visit our Blog.\n\nThis site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of\nService apply.\n\nPowered by\n\nPrivacy PolicySecurityVulnerability Disclosure\n\n", "frontpage": false}
